message.content: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper discusses a model for visual question answering that takes both image and textual inputs, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of paragraph captions generated by an encoder-decoder model also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the model's performance is evaluated using metrics such as accuracy and F1 score, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
